Description: Fragment of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Oval handle at neck join. Circular stamp with Helios head symbol. Clay near fine light brown.
Curator's comments: Drawn by Petrie (Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 200, 5 or 173, 15). Name Euphranor. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Musaeum, ABC 0360.30.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1040)
